### Identify deceptive patterns in UX design  
具有欺骗性的、误导性的  
to buy、to use 
​Deceptive patterns are ethically ​wrong and not a good business practice.  

1、Forced continuity is the practice of charging ​a user for membership without a warning or a reminder.   
2、sneak into basket, ​extra things had been added to your cart   
​3、Hidden costs is similar to sneak into basket, ​except there are extra charges in ​your cart instead of extra products.  
  you might be booking movie tickets online, ​but when you reach the final checkout page, ​there are suddenly online booking fees. ​    
4、confirmshaming, which is when users are made to feel ​guilty when they opt out of something.  
5、urgency, They convince you that you need ​to purchase an item before you ​run out of time or miss today's amazing price.    
6、scarcity, a website makes you very ​aware of the limited number of items in stock.   
  This injustice scarcity of the product is intended to ​manipulate you and the numbers are often fake  


